value.name: Ir geminorum: complex disk behavior during quiescence
value.snippet: IR Gem is a member of the SU UMa subclass of dwarf novae. SU UMa stars are identified by their distinctive superoutbursts and the accompanying superhumps phenomena (see .6 for a comprehensive review). discovered IR Gem to be an SU UMa star and carried out the first systematic investigation.

value.name: Eta Geminorum - Wikipedia
value.snippet: η Geminorum is a triple system, with the luminous class M star having a close companion known only from radial velocity variations, and a more distant companion resolved visually. In 1881, Burnham observed that η Geminorum had a close companion (η Gem B). At that time the separation was measured to be 1.08". [24]
